div1.ab: In Justices Court - Before T.H. Cann, Justice of the Peace.
Territory of Washington, plaintiff vs. William Spears and James McGough Defendants | Territory of Washington County of King. -ss.
To the Sheriff or any Constable of said County, Greeting:
div1.p: Whereas, Bernard McCronney has this day complained in writing, under oath, to the undersigned, one of the Justices of the Peace in and for said County, that on the 26th day of October 1883, t Seattle in said County William Spears and James McGough did commit the crime of obtaining money by false pretenses.
Therefore, in the name of the United States, you are commanded forthwith to apprehend the said William Spears and James McGough and bring him them before me, to be dealt with according to law.
div1.ab: Given under my hand this second day of November 1883
TH Cann Justice of the Peace, Seattle Precinct, King County, W.T.
Filed Nov 2 1883. TH Cann Justice of the Peace
